Title: Critical Phenomenon and Phase Separation in 3 He-4 He Mixtures  
Author: Erik Draeger 
Note: Typeset using REVT  
Date: (May 5, 1998)  
Address: 61801  
Affiliation: Department of Physics, University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign,  E X  
Abstract: This paper is a brief survey of 3 He-4 He mixtures, with special attention to critical phenomenon. The phase diagram in the T-X plane is discussed, as well as the ability of phenomenological Landau theory to explain it. Landau theory is then applied to the T- plane, with more successful results. The Siggia-Nelson model is briefly mentioned. Finally, the details of phase separation are presented, with discussion about the meaning and derivation of the spinodal lines which bound the unstable and metastable parts of the two phase region.
